cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.CC

This paper deals with the interdefinability of two formalisms, namely defeasible logic and logic programming, and provides a method of translating between them. This makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the well-founded semantics for normal logic programs, which falls under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also introduces antimonotone operators based on the Gelfond-Lifschitz operator, which is relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Computation and Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
